{
  "analysis": "We are at /app with an empty-looking screen. The task is to install and build BVLC Caffe v1.0.0 for CPU-only, prepare CIFAR-10 data, run training for exactly 500 iterations, capture the training output to /app/caffe/training_output.txt, verify that final test accuracy (averaged over 100 test iterations) is >45% and within 5% of train accuracy, and ensure the snapshot model file examples/cifar10/cifar10_quick_iter_500.caffemodel exists. We need system packages (build-essential, protobuf, glog, gflags, atlas/openblas, hdf5, leveldb, lmdb, snappy, boost, git). We'll clone caffe into /app/caffe, set CPU_ONLY and disable OpenCV to simplify build, build caffe and tools, download and convert CIFAR-10, adjust the solver to run exactly 500 iters, snapshot at 500, test over 100 iters and at iter 500, then run training with output tee'd to file. After training, we'll check for the model file and parse the log to verify accuracy constraints. If training accuracy isn't logged, we'll handle by computing (but likely the train_test prototxt logs it).",
  "plan": "- Update apt and install build dependencies for BVLC Caffe CPU-only without OpenCV to avoid compatibility issues.\n- Clone BVLC Caffe into /app/caffe and checkout the v1.0.0 tag.\n- Configure Makefile.config: enable CPU_ONLY and disable OpenCV (USE_OPENCV := 0). Keep default BLAS (ATLAS) and other defaults.\n- Build caffe binaries and tools (no python bindings).\n- Download CIFAR-10 and create LMDB datasets using provided scripts.\n- Adjust the CIFAR-10 quick solver to run max_iter=500, snapshot=500, test_iter=100, test_interval=500 so that it tests at the end and snapshots the required model.\n- Run training with logging redirected to /app/caffe/training_output.txt.\n- Verify the existence of the model file examples/cifar10/cifar10_quick_iter_500.caffemodel.\n- Parse training_output.txt to extract the final test accuracy (averaged over 100 iters) and the last reported train accuracy, then check that test accuracy > 45% and is not more than 5% below train accuracy. Output the computed values and whether constraints are satisfied.",
